<body>

<h3><i>I update one of my attributes repeatedly.</i> </h3>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
<p><b>UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY</b></p>
<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
<pre>substitute-text-area-for attribute-name my-attribute                   
substitute-text-area-for attribute-expression my-attribute + 1                                         
substitute-text-area-for time-period 1
substitute-text-area-for comment Notes                                                                      
do-every time-period
   [set attribute-name 
        attribute-expression]
;comment</pre>
<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
<h2>Variants</h2>
<p>You can change the name and the expression for updating the attribute.</p>
<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>
<p><a href="UPDATE-PARAMETER-REPEATEDLY.html">UPDATE-PARAMETER-REPEATEDLY</a> 
updates a model parameter repeatedly.</p>
<h2>How this works</h2>
<p>This uses the NetLogo <b>SET</b> primitive command to name the parameter and 
to update its value to the value of the expression. It uses the BehaviourComposer <b>
<a target="_top" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/programming-guide#toc0">do-every</a></b> command to schedule the 
updates repeatedly.</p>
<h2>History</h2>
<p><a href="UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY.html">UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY</a> was implemented by Ken Kahn on 9 November 2009. </p>

